The change is in platform/browser-extension/src/tab-state.ts in the checkTabStateChanges function around line 220-229. After the sendToServer call that sends tab.stateChanged, add a forwardToSidePanel call:

forwardToSidePanel({
  type: 'sp:serverMessage',
  data: {
    jsonrpc: '2.0',
    method: 'tab.stateChanged',
    params: { plugin: plugin.name, state: newState.state, tabId: newState.tabId, url: newState.url },
  },
});

Import forwardToSidePanel from './messaging.js'. The same pattern should be applied in handlePluginUpdate in message-router.ts (around line 309-319) where it computes new tab state and sends to server — also forward to side panel there.

Also need to forward tab state in sendTabSyncAll (tab-state.ts around line 107-113). After sending tab.syncAll to the server, forward individual tab.stateChanged messages to the side panel for each plugin so the side panel gets initial tab states on connect without waiting for fetchConfigState.

The side panel handler at App.tsx:83-93 already handles tab.stateChanged correctly — it pattern-matches the plugin name and updates tabState in the plugins array. No changes needed on the side panel side for this story.

This is the most impactful change. The key insight: handleSyncFull in message-router.ts already has validated plugin payloads (the `metas` array). It needs to build the ConfigStatePlugin[] shape from these and forward it.

In message-router.ts handleSyncFull (around line 289):
1. Import a new getPluginTabState function from tab-state.ts that reads lastKnownState
2. Build the plugins array in ConfigStatePlugin format:
   metas.map(m => ({
     name: m.name,
     displayName: m.displayName ?? m.name,
     version: m.version,
     trustTier: m.trustTier,
     tabState: getPluginTabState(m.name),
     urlPatterns: m.urlPatterns,
     tools: m.tools, // already has { name, description, enabled }
   }))
3. Forward via forwardToSidePanel({ type: 'sp:serverMessage', data: { jsonrpc: '2.0', method: 'plugins.state', params: { plugins } } })
4. Replace the current synthetic 'plugins.changed' notification

In tab-state.ts, add and export:
const getPluginTabState = (pluginName: string): TabState => lastKnownState.get(pluginName) ?? 'closed';

In App.tsx, add a handler for 'plugins.state' before the existing 'plugins.changed' handler:
if (data.method === 'plugins.state' && data.params) {
  const params = data.params as { plugins?: PluginState[] };
  if (Array.isArray(params.plugins)) {
    setPlugins(params.plugins);
  }
  sendResponse({ ok: true });
  return true;
}

Keep 'plugins.changed' handler as a fallback (it still triggers fetchConfigState), but the primary path is now 'plugins.state'.

IMPORTANT: The tab state in the pushed data may be slightly stale (lastKnownState reflects the state BEFORE sendTabSyncAll runs after sync.full). This is acceptable because US-001 ensures real-time tab state updates flow separately. The side panel gets an approximate state immediately, then precise state updates moments later via tab.stateChanged.

Same pattern as US-002 but for a single plugin update.

In message-router.ts handlePluginUpdate (around line 322):
1. Import getPluginTabState from tab-state.ts (already imported from US-002)
2. Build the single plugin in ConfigStatePlugin format from the validated meta
3. Forward: forwardToSidePanel({ type: 'sp:serverMessage', data: { jsonrpc: '2.0', method: 'plugin.updated', params: { plugin: { name, displayName, version, trustTier, tabState: getPluginTabState(meta.name), urlPatterns, tools } } } })
4. Replace the current synthetic 'plugins.changed' notification

In App.tsx, add handler for 'plugin.updated':
if (data.method === 'plugin.updated' && data.params) {
  const params = data.params as { plugin?: PluginState };
  if (params.plugin && typeof params.plugin.name === 'string') {
    const updated = params.plugin;
    setPlugins(prev => {
      const idx = prev.findIndex(p => p.name === updated.name);
      if (idx >= 0) {
        const next = [...prev];
        next[idx] = updated;
        return next;
      }
      return [...prev, updated];
    });
  }
  sendResponse({ ok: true });
  return true;
}

Add 'plugin.updated' to SIDE_PANEL_METHODS set in message-router.ts.

In App.tsx, remove the entire block from 'Fallback: ws:message with sync.full...' comment through 'return false;' (approximately lines 118-134 after US-002/US-003 changes, but find the exact block by searching for 'ws:message' in the listener).

The block looks like:
